article.headline: Appalachian St. 77, Lees-McRae 44
article.story: BOONE, N.C. -- Isaac Butts scored 22 points on 11-of-12 shooting and Appalachian State defeated Lees-McRae 77-44 on Tuesday night. The Mountaineers (2-1) used a 16-4 run in a span of 5:17, including seven points from Marcus Wright, to break an 8-8 tie. Donald Sims capped the run with three free throws to give Appalachian State a 24-12 lead with 12 minutes left in the first half. Appalachian State shot 54.4 percent from the field (31 of 57) and outrebounded the Bobcats 39-28. Butts led the Mountaineers with nine rebounds. Lees-McRae trailed 43-26 at halftime before shooting just 27.6 percent in the second half (8 of 29). Adam McFerran and Sam Youse led the Bobcats with 16 and 15 points. Youse finished 3-for-8 from 3-point range as Lees-McRae made just 20 percent from the outside (5 of 25).
